HEADWORD: Thallus
<hw>Thal"lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Thalli</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ young shoot
or branch, frond.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A solid mass of cellular
tissue, consisting of one or more layers, usually in the form of a flat
stratum or expansion, but sometimes erect or pendulous, and elongated
and branching, and forming the substance of the thallogens.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

